The paper deals with a task of visual question answering, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a scalable, jointly trained, end-to-end formulation to this problem, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of latest advances in image representation and natural language processing, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper also discusses the analysis of human consensus and the use of metrics, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
